\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 RepQuarks is a code management mechanism for SuperCollider based on Quarks. 
\b0 \
\
Authors: Martin Carle and Ioannis Zannos, 2011-2012. \
\
The source code for RepQuarks is currently included in the SC repository on Github. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/iani/SC"}}{\fldrslt https://github.com/iani/SC}}  under folder "PutMyAliasInExtensions". \
\

\b\fs36 Installation Instructions\

\b0\fs24 \
You can use the RepQuarks class without the library that it is part of, by putting a copy or alias of the RepClass.sc file in the Extensions folder of your 
\f1 Platform.userAppSupportDir
\f0 . \
\
Alternatively, if you want to use the rest of the quarks belonging to the library which contains RepQuarks, the make an alias of the folder "PutMyAliasInExtensions" and put it in the Extensions folder of your Platform.userAppSupportDir. Recompile SuperCollider and choose any quarks you want to include from the Quarks menu. Press the save button. Recompile the SuperCollider library when the message on the Quarks window tells you to. \
\
